---
description: Test-first policy for behavior bugs and regressions
globs: "tests/**/*.test.js"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Test-First Regressions

- For behavior bugs, add or extend a failing regression test before implementing the fix.
- After implementing the fix, run `npm test` and report pass/fail clearly.
- Prefer assertions on observable behavior (generated rule JSON, matching outcomes), not implementation details.
- Add at least one edge-case assertion when bug root cause involves encoding/escaping/parsing differences.
- Keep tests deterministic with mocks for browser APIs (`chrome.*`) where runtime APIs are unavailable.
